               <note type="summary">This document is a letter from Governor John
				Sevier (1796-1801, 1803-1809) to Joseph Anderson, William Cocke, and William C.
				Claiborne, dated February 26, 1800. This letter is about William Augustus
				Bowles and his influence over the Creek Nation. Sevier is telling the men to be
				prepared for what is to come, which could possibly be a war. Sevier stated that
				the state of Tennessee is particularly vulnerable to hostilities and
				violence.</note>
